@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

top to bottom direction
title FIG-12-05. Horizon Bank Payment Attack Tree

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "Root goal\nCause an unauthorised or prohibited\noutgoing payment to be released" as Root
rectangle "Alternative attack paths\nOR" as OrNode

rectangle "T12-01\nStolen or replayed\ncustomer session creates\na payment" as T1201
rectangle "T12-02\nPayment amount or beneficiary\nis tampered with between\nchannel and platform" as T1202
rectangle "T12-03\nStolen service credential\nis used to submit\na posting request" as T1203
rectangle "T12-05\nMisuse or compromise\nprivileged financial-crime\nrelease authority" as T1205
rectangle "T12-07\nWeak entitlement or ownership\nvalidation permits payment\nfrom the wrong account" as T1207
rectangle "T12-08\nOperations repair misuse path" as T1208
rectangle "AND" as And1208
rectangle "Operations repair authority\ncan modify an eligible payment" as T1208a
rectangle "Required separation of duties\nis absent, bypassed\nor incorrectly enforced" as T1208b

rectangle "Mitigation note\nstrong authentication,\nsession protection,\nstep-up triggers" as M1201 #FFF8DC
rectangle "Mitigation note\nmessage integrity,\nrequest validation,\nimmutable audit event" as M1202 #FFF8DC
rectangle "Mitigation note\nservice identity,\nstate validation,\ncredential rotation" as M1203 #FFF8DC
rectangle "Mitigation note\ncase assignment,\nrole check,\nexception evidence" as M1205 #FFF8DC
rectangle "Mitigation note\nownership check,\nentitlement validation,\ndeny by default" as M1207 #FFF8DC
rectangle "Mitigation note\nmaker-checker rule,\nrepair-state validation,\nrelease audit" as M1208 #FFF8DC

Root --> OrNode
OrNode --> T1201 : OR
OrNode --> T1202 : OR
OrNode --> T1203 : OR
OrNode --> T1205 : OR
OrNode --> T1207 : OR
OrNode --> T1208 : OR
T1208 --> And1208
And1208 --> T1208a
And1208 --> T1208b

T1201 ..> M1201 : mitigation
T1202 ..> M1202 : mitigation
T1203 ..> M1203 : mitigation
T1205 ..> M1205 : mitigation
T1207 ..> M1207 : mitigation
T1208 ..> M1208 : mitigation

legend bottom
Solid arrows are attack-tree paths. Dotted arrows point to mitigation notes.
OR means any listed attack path may contribute to the root goal.
The T12-08 AND node means both child conditions are required for that path.
Excluded threats: T12-04 concerns attribution and evidence. T12-06 concerns excessive event-data exposure.
Neither directly achieves this attack tree's root goal.
endlegend
@enduml
